  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The validation requirement mandates a controlled-experiment methodology; the supporting validation activity was conducted as an observational study drawing on pump-registry flow measurements. The narrative treats the two approaches as complementary and equivalent, but the structured activityType field records 'observational-study', which does not satisfy the 'controlled-experiment' requiredVerificationMethod. This is the targeted W-AR-03 inference-method mismatch. Decision recorded as Accepted.",
